I have identified and implemented a fix for the bug in the CharacterReader class. The issue was in the `bufferUp()` method where the code was using the requested number of characters to skip (`bufPos`) instead of the actual number of characters skipped, which is returned by the `reader.skip()` method.

The fix changes:
```java
reader.skip(bufPos);
// ...
readerPos += bufPos;
```

To:
```java
long skipped = reader.skip(bufPos);
// ...
readerPos += skipped;
```

This ensures that the logical position (`readerPos`) is updated correctly based on the actual number of characters that were skipped by the underlying reader, which may be less than the requested amount. This is important because `Reader.skip()` is not guaranteed to skip the full requested number of characters.

The diff of the changes is saved in `blind_fix.patch`.

